# TypeScript / React

- Use strict typing; avoid `any` unless interfacing with untyped third-party data.
- Path alias: `@/` — use it consistently for imports.
- Prefer function components and hooks; follow existing naming (PascalCase files).
- Colocate tests with components when the repo already does (`*.test.tsx` next to source).

**Example — imports**

```tsx
// Good
import { Button } from "@//components/ui/button";

// Avoid deep relative chains when alias exists
import { Button } from "../../../components/ui/button";
```